According to the student pilot, during the landing roll the airplane began to weathervane 
toward the edge of the runway and the left wing began to lift up. He added engine power in an 
attempt to stop the swerve; however, the airplane exited the runway and ground looped, 
sustaining substantial damage to the fuselage. At the time this report was completed, the pilot 
had not submitted NTSB form 6120.1, Pilot/Operator Accident/Incident Report as requested.
The student pilot's loss of directional control during landing, which resulted in a ground loop.
